# Where to put these:
#
# • Vercel (Production + Preview + Development): DATABASE_URL* / POSTGRES_* / NEON_* — usually
#   injected by the Neon integration or `vercel env pull`. Also set JWT_SECRET (and optional
#   ADMIN_SETUP_SECRET) in Project → Settings → Environment Variables, or via API/CLI.
#
# • Local machine — pick ONE style (do not commit secrets):
#   - `.env.development.local` — Vite + `vercel dev` / `vercel env pull` (gitignored)
#   - `.env` — same, if you prefer; keep it gitignored
#
# • Seed script only (local): DEFAULT_ADMIN_EMAIL / DEFAULT_ADMIN_PASSWORD — not needed on Vercel.
#
# • Never commit: passwords, DATABASE_URL with credentials, JWT_SECRET, VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN.

# Neon — pooled URL recommended for serverless (see Neon dashboard).
# On Vercel, the Neon/Postgres integration may set POSTGRES_URL only; the API accepts DATABASE_URL,
# POSTGRES_URL, or POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL (first one wins).
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST/DB?sslmode=require

# API auth — min 16 characters; must match between local API and Vercel serverless
JWT_SECRET=your-long-random-secret-here

# Optional: enables POST /api/auth/register with body { email, password, setupSecret }
ADMIN_SETUP_SECRET=

# One-time seed (pnpm db:seed) — local only. Scripts load .env → .env.local → .env.development.local
# (same idea as Vite; put secrets in .env.development.local if you use that file).
DEFAULT_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@yourdomain.com
DEFAULT_ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# Add another admin user (run once per user; do not commit real values):
# NEW_USER_EMAIL=someone@example.com NEW_USER_PASSWORD='your-password' pnpm db:add-user
#
# Debug “login works in DB but not in browser”: same DATABASE_URL as API, then:
# VERIFY_EMAIL=you@example.com VERIFY_PASSWORD='your-password' pnpm db:verify-login

# Local dev — easiest: `pnpm dev:local` (API :3000 + Vite :5173). It sets VITE_USE_LOCAL_API=1 so
# `VITE_API_BASE_URL` is ignored and /api is proxied to localhost (avoids CORS to production).
# Or two terminals: pnpm dev:vercel  then  pnpm dev — for that, comment out VITE_API_BASE_URL below.
# Or hit the live site’s API (no vercel dev). Live domain:
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://cyansphotos.com
# VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:3000

# Production on https://cyansphotos.com: leave VITE_API_BASE_URL unset so /api is same-origin.

# Admin image uploads — file bytes go to Vercel Blob; Neon only stores the public URL on each photo row.
# Without this token, POST /api/upload returns 503 ("Upload storage is not configured").
#
# --- Option A: Vercel CLI (from repo root, project linked via `vercel link`) ---
# 1. pnpm vercel:blob:create -- cyan-photography-blob
#    (pick any unused store name). When prompted: link to this project = Yes.
#    Then select Production, Preview, and Development (space toggles, Enter confirms).
# 2. pnpm vercel:env:pull   → writes Development env (incl. BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN) to .env.development.local
# 3. Redeploy production on Vercel so Preview/Production pick up the new env var if not already.
#
# --- Option B: Dashboard ---
# Vercel → Project → Storage → Blob → Create / link store → env var BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN on the project.
# Local: copy the token into .env.development.local or run `pnpm vercel:env:pull`.
#
# Docs: https://vercel.com/docs/storage/vercel-blob | CLI: https://vercel.com/docs/cli/blob
BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=

# Optional: comma-separated extra origins for /api CORS (defaults include localhost:5173 + cyansphotos.com)
# CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5174,https://staging.example.com
